Lady Gaga was certainly all shades of delighted after her win at the Oscars. The singer and actress’s winning song Shallow from the musical film, A Star Is Born earned her the Best Original Oscar. With her recent win, she has become the first person ever to win an Oscar, Grammy, BAFTA and Golden Globe in a single year. Read More: Here Is The List Of Oscar Winners In Major Categories Giving off an emotional and victorious speech, Lady Gaga thanked her co-star Bradley Cooper while receiving her award, “There is not a single person on the planet that could sing this song but you.” It is also noteworthy to add that she is the first to ever be nominated for both Best Actress and Best Original Song in the same year. Gaga who has now sealed her acting genius in the Hollywood sands of time was visibly excited and showed emotions, each conveying her different levels.